    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'The Game based Learning and Digital Experiences (GLaDE) Laboratory at
    the University of Florida develops interactive tools that help students learn
    difficult engineering concepts through visualization, experimentation, and game
    based environments.


    Many foundational courses such as statics, thermodynamics,
    and dynamics are essential to engineering education but are often challenging
    and discouraging for students. GLaDE explores how virtual reality, simulation,
    and interactive problem solving can improve motivation, conceptual understanding,
    and engagement in these subjects.


    This project is part of an ongoing effort
    to design learning experiences that support active exploration rather than passive
    memorization. By combining physics based interaction with structured problem
    solving tasks, the goal is to help students better understand core engineering
    principles and build confidence as they learn.


    The GLaDE Laboratory is
    led by Dr. Philip Jackson in the Department of Engineering Education at the University
    of Florida. Student researchers in the lab design and evaluate new digital learning
    environments that study how emerging technologies such as virtual reality and
    adaptive simulations influence student motivation, performance, and understanding
    in engineering education.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
